{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778347126,"nonce":"3EPqrhxNoCRk3lZ9filKUfVml40=","message":"## Anti-anticipation 6-cell matrix outcomes (pre-reg `2bc95fd`)\n\nCross-cutting training-method observations from the 6-cell matrix run (commit `b5e6e6c`):\n\n**Strong candidate emerging:** `gru__jerk + nn_output_pre_go=1e-2 + nn_hidden_derivative=1e2` (the \"combo\" cell). Across 5 replicates:\n- Variance ratio (SD/mean peak vel) = **0.007** — effectively pinned to a single attractor\n- Hold-period forward drift = **4.6 mm** vs control 19.8 mm (77% suppression)\n- Peak forward velocity = 1.22 m/s (highest of all cells; ~2× control)\n\n**Per-lever findings:**\n- **`nn_output_pre_go` (1e-2)** *does* suppress hold-period drift on its own (5.5 mm), but does NOT collapse pre-go motor activity to zero — the term's weighted contribution rises monotonically through training (~2e-4 → 1.6e-1). The penalty slows growth, doesn't kill it.\n- **`nn_hidden_derivative` (1e2)** alone collapses replicate variance dramatically (VR=0.006) and produces fast reaches (1.07 m/s), but *increases* anticipation drift by 80% (35.7 mm). On its own it's a bad anti-anticipation lever; in combination with motor_pre it's exactly what we want.\n- **Loss-shape variants (Variant A: terminal velocity only; Variant B: historical (t/N)^6 + terminal cliff)** did NOT deliver: variance ratios 0.14 and 0.19 respectively, anticipation drifts comparable to control. **Deprioritize loss-shape as an anti-anticipation lever** until proven otherwise on a different metric.\n\n**Method-side implication:** the \"combo\" loss-config (motor_pre + smooth_high) is a candidate default for the standard-backprop training method going forward. Not promoting yet — first need to (a) verify on the prior matrix's RMSE-ratio metric (see analysis caveat on `4d38c15`), and (b) check that the suppressed anticipation generalizes to held-out conditions.\n\nSee `results/part2_5/runpod/anti_anticipation_loss_shape_6cell/notes/variance_analysis.md` for the full table.","files":null}]}